K8s services:
-----------
- ClusterIP -> Default and available only withing cluter
- NodePort -> port is reserved on each node. Accessible outside cluster
- LoadBalancer -> NodePort + external LB -> LB to the ports


Envoy:
------
- It is a proxy. Proxy usually handles cross cutting concerns like TLS, Auth, RETRY
- Envoy acts like a sidecar next to container in a pod.
- Request will go to container via Envoy.